17 Section 138. A. Except as otherwise provided by law, every
18 inmate of a state correctional institution shall have their his or
19 her term of imprisonment reduced monthly, based upon the class level
20 to which they are assigned. Earned credits may be subtracted from
21 the total credits accumulated by an inmate, upon recommendation of
22 the institution’s disciplinary committee, following due process, and
23 upon approval of the warden or superintendent. Each earned credit
24 is equivalent to one (1) day of incarceration. Lost credits may be
