4 F. The policy and procedure developed by the Department of
5 Corrections shall include provisions for adjustment review
6 committees of not less than three members for each such committee.
7 Each committee shall consist of a classification team supervisor who
8 shall act as chairman, the case manager for the inmate being
9 reviewed or classified, a correctional officer or inmate counselor,
10 and not more than two other members, if deemed necessary, determined
11 pursuant to policy and procedure to be appropriate for the specific
12 adjustment review committee or committees to which they are
13 assigned. At least once every four (4) months the adjustment review
14 committee for each inmate shall evaluate the class level status and
15 performance of the inmate and determine whether or not the class
16 level for the inmate should be changed.
17 Any inmate who feels aggrieved by a decision made by an
18 adjustment review committee may utilize normal grievance procedures
19 in effect with the Department of Corrections and in effect at the
20 facility in which the inmate is incarcerated.
